PRIVACY POLICY — FIXATION

Last updated: July 5, 2026


WHO WE ARE

Fixation is published by Kerri Williams. If you have questions about this
policy, contact us at tmrw.pod@gmail.com.


WHAT WE COLLECT AND WHY

Reading lists and preferences.
When you use Fixation, you can save series to your personal reading list
(Want to Read, Currently Reading, Completed, Dropped, On Hold), rate
titles, and filter by trope preferences. This data is stored to power your
personal library and recommendations, and is associated with your account
so it persists across sessions.

Community content.
If you post discussion comments, create community lists, or otherwise
contribute content visible to other users, that content is stored and may
be visible to other Fixation users. Do not include personal information
in anything you post publicly, since community content is, by nature,
seen by other members.

Device identifier / account identifier.
We generate and store an identifier tied to your account to associate your
reading lists, preferences, and any community content with you. This
identifier is not linked to your real name or contact information unless
you choose to provide that information yourself (for example, in a
username or profile bio).

Subscription status.
We use RevenueCat to manage subscriptions. RevenueCat receives your app
store account's anonymous subscriber ID to verify your subscription
status. We do not receive or store your payment details — those are
handled entirely by Apple or Google. RevenueCat's privacy policy is
available at revenuecat.com/privacy.

Usage data.
We may collect basic usage data (such as which features are used and how
often) to understand how Fixation is used and to improve the app.


WHAT WE DO NOT COLLECT

We do not host or distribute copyrighted manga or manhwa content ourselves.
Fixation links out to third-party, officially licensed platforms for
reading — we do not collect data about what you read on those external
platforms. We do not sell your data to anyone, ever. We do not use your
data for third-party advertising.


THIRD PARTIES

We share data with the following third parties, limited to what is
necessary to operate the service:

- RevenueCat — subscription management (anonymous subscriber ID and
  purchase status)
- Our hosting provider — your account data (reading lists, preferences,
  community content) is stored on secure servers

We link out to third-party officially licensed reading platforms (such as
Webtoon, Lezhin, Tappytoon, Manta, and similar services) as part of
Fixation's core recommendation feature. Once you leave Fixation to read on
one of these platforms, their own privacy policy governs your data, not
this one. We encourage you to review the privacy policy of any external
platform you use.


DATA STORAGE AND SECURITY

Your account data is stored on secure servers. We use industry-standard
encryption for data in transit and at rest.


YOUR RIGHTS AND CONTROLS

You can export your data or delete your account and all associated data
at any time from within the app's Settings. Deletion is permanent and
complete. If you are located in the EU, UK, or California, you have
additional rights under GDPR and CCPA respectively, including the right
to access, correct, or delete your personal data. Contact us at
tmrw.pod@gmail.com to exercise any of these rights.


COMMUNITY CONTENT AND MODERATION

Content you post in community features (discussion, lists, comments) may
be visible to other users of Fixation. We reserve the right to remove
content that violates our Terms of Use. If you believe another user's
content violates our terms or your rights, contact us at
tmrw.pod@gmail.com.


CHILDREN

Fixation is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has
provided us with personal information, contact us and we will delete it
promptly.


CHANGES TO THIS POLICY

If we make material changes to how we collect or use data, we will update
this page and change the "last updated" date at the top. Continued use of
the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.


